      "id": "RQ-0045",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Inventory the full current agent-browser surface from version-matched sources",
      "description": "Build the source-of-truth capability inventory for the currently installed upstream agent-browser before changing wrapper behavior. Do not rely on root `--help` alone: include `agent-browser skills list`, `agent-browser skills get core --full`, root help, and relevant subcommand help for command families that have nested options. Capture commands that root help omits but the core skill documents, such as `state`, `frame`, `dialog`, `window`, key down/up aliases, wait predicates, snapshot URL output, tab labels, and screenshot annotation/full-page options. Acceptance criteria: the canonical baseline lists the target version and the complete command/flag/env/skill surface this package intends to support; verifier tests fail on version drift, missing required human-authored doc tokens, and missing upstream tokens; no browser-runtime support changes are made in this inventory task.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": ["agent-browser", "upstream-sync", "baseline", "docs", "verification"],
      "scope": [
        "scripts/agent-browser-capability-baseline.mjs",
        "scripts/check-command-reference-baseline.mjs",
        "scripts/verify-command-reference.mjs",
        "test/verify-command-reference.test.ts",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "agent_browser { args: [\"--version\"] }",
        "agent_browser { args: [\"--help\"] }",
        "agent_browser { args: [\"skills\", \"list\"] }",
        "agent_browser { args: [\"skills\", \"get\", \"core\", \"--full\"] }"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"--version\"] } :: current installed upstream is `agent-browser 0.26.0`.",
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"--help\"] } :: root help includes current command families such as `skills`, `keyboard`, `stream`, `auth`, `chat`, `dashboard`, setup commands, providers, config/env, and iOS examples.",
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"skills\", \"get\", \"core\", \"--full\"] } :: version-matched core skill documents additional surface not visible in the pasted root help, including `state`, `frame`, `dialog`, `window`, wait predicate flags, tab labels, and detailed auth/session patterns.",
        "path: scripts/agent-browser-capability-baseline.mjs:15-63 :: current canonical metadata samples only root/tab/snapshot/wait help and a finite token list, so the full skill/subcommand surface is not yet the source of truth.",
        "path: scripts/verify-command-reference.mjs:83-107 :: verifier checks only the tokens declared in the canonical baseline and therefore cannot catch omissions outside that token list."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Collect root help, skills list, core full skill, and targeted subcommand help needed to enumerate the complete surface for the installed version.",
        "Refactor the capability baseline into explicit sections for commands, command groups, global options, environment variables, providers, setup/diagnostic commands, and version-matched upstream skills.",
        "Expand verifier coverage so both upstream expectations and human-authored docs are checked against the complete baseline, not only a small root-help sample.",
        "Update generated baseline blocks and tests without changing runtime behavior in this task."
      ],
