        "npm test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"skills\", \"list\"] } :: native passthrough already returns JSON skill metadata, but no dedicated contract asserts the shape or presentation.",
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"skills\", \"get\", \"core\", \"--full\"] } :: output compacts to a full-output path, which should become an explicit supported contract.",
        "workflow: agent_browser { args: [\"--help\"] } :: current model-facing help output redacts harmless example text such as bearer-token/proxy examples, showing inspection output redaction needs a narrower contract.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:88-91 :: plain-text inspection is limited to help/version flags and does not explicitly model upstream `skills` inspection commands.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts:1328-1386 :: presentation is generic unless command-specific handling is added."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Classify `skills` and help/version flows as safe inspection-style calls where they should not allocate or mutate the managed browser session unless upstream requires it.",
        "Add presentation summaries for skill lists, skill documents, and skill paths, with large-output spill behavior preserved.",
        "Tighten redaction so documentation/example tokens are readable while actual secrets in args, env-derived details, and result fields remain masked.",
        "Add fake-upstream tests plus a real-upstream shape fixture update for the inspection/skills surface."
