      "description": "Audit and update argument parsing, command identification, value-flag validation, session planning, and non-interactive behavior against the full current surface. The wrapper should continue to be thin, but it must not misclassify new command families or accidentally run interactive/long-lived/destructive flows without clear docs and safe contracts. Cover command-level flags with values (`find --name`, wait predicates, tab labels, network filters/bodies, profiler categories, cookie attributes, auth options, dashboard/stream ports, chat model/quiet/verbose flags, etc.), launch-scoped global options, provider flags, and setup commands such as `install`, `upgrade`, and `doctor --fix`. Acceptance criteria: runtime tests pin command/subcommand extraction and validation across the full baseline; unsupported `stdin` remains rejected; long-running or interactive flows have explicit behavior and recovery guidance; `npm test` passes.",
